        <page n="01" image="pa.fr.vs.1864.12.21.01">
            <div type="a">
                <column>5</column>
                <head>Address: To the Democratic Citizens of Pennsylvania</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Fictitious ballots have been placed in the ballot-boxes, answering to
                    false registries, the same as have been repeatedly proven to have been the case
                    in our elections heretofore; and, secondly, the suffrages of the volunteer
                    soldiers have not only been over-awed and perverted by corrupt partisan
                    officials, but the returns themselves, in many cases, have been tampered with
                    and transformed."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>C. L. Ward, Chairman</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>The Democratic State Central Committee Chairman outlines various fraudulent
                    activities that gave the Republicans the victory in the November election.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>7</column>
                <head>How to Keep a Cow</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Offers suggestions for raising a cow economically by growing a garden.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Classified ads, columns 1-4</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="pa.fr.vs.1864.12.21.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Great Enterprises</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Urges the president to take the blame for his failures in addition to
                    taking credit for his successes, as he has recently done.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Democracy and the Union</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"We honestly believe had the Democratic party been successful in the late
                    political contest we would have had peace and reunion, in thirty days after it
                    obtained power, without the dishonor or degradation to either side."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Emphasizes that the Democrats are the ones who truly want the Union
                    restored. Accuses the secessionists and the Lincoln administration of being
                    "equally hostile" to the Union.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Presidential Election--Official</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Publishes the official vote tallies from each Pennsylvania county in the
                    November election. In Franklin County, McClellan received a total of 3821, while
                    Lincoln received 3862. In the entire state, Democrats received 276,308 votes,
                    while Republicans received 296,389.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>The Church and Politics</head>
                <origin>German Reformed Messenger</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"It is a great mistake to suppose that the Church hallows politics by
                    becoming itself political. . . . Denominations, congregations, and ministers who
                    forget their calling in this matter, will themselves be secularized before they
                    are aware of it."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Argues that ministers do not belong in political affairs.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Reports of troop movement in Georgia and Tennessee, columns 5-6; classified
                ads, column 7</pageNote>
        </page>
